race.comment: MIDNIGHT OPAL (15) smart gelding with a good record at this trip. Set to peak third-up after knocking up late when third to Carbonados over 1200m at Randwick. Jumps in class but will relish the drop in weight from the gate. Winning rider hops back on and this looks a target race. BRAVE ONE (14) shouldered the 61.5kg first-up when a closing second over the unsuitable 1100m at Randwick. Gets map favours and shapes as the main danger. JUST PARTY (12) talented gelding resuming after having mixed luck in group company last prep. Looks set to explode after the two trials and goes into the exotics. MAYFAIR (4) forget the run in the Golden Eagle, and has slim place claims from the awkward draw.
